 systems have worked together, and sometimes competed, to provide solutions for local problems. Idioms of Sámi Health and Healing is one of the first English-language studies of the Traditional Healing methods among the Sámi, and offers valuable insight and academic context to those in the fields of anthropology, medical anthropology, transcultural psychiatry, and circumpolar studies. Idioms of Sámi Health and Healing is the second volume in the Patterns of Northern Traditional Healing series. Contributors: Kjell Birkely Andersen, Anne Karen Hætta, Mona Anita Kiil, Britt Kramvig, Trine Kvitberg, Stein R. Mathisen, Barbara Helen Miller, Marit Myrvoll, Randi Inger Johanne Nymo, Sigvald Persen.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aHealingzEurope, Northern. 0aSami (European people)xHealth and hygienezEurope, Northern. 0aSami (European people)xMedicinezEurope, Northern. 7aMEDICAL / Healing.2bisacsh  aNorthern Studies/Traditional Healing/Health.1 aAndersen, Kjell Birkely, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAnderson, David G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaetta, Anne Karen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHætta, Anne Karen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKiil, Mona Anita, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKramvig, Britt, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKvitberg, Trine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMathisen, Stein R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMiller, Barbara Helen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMiller, Barbara Helen, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMyrvoll, 